Package: cooccure
Title: Co-Occurrence Networks from Any Data Format
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mohammed", "Saqr", email = "saqr@saqr.me",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Sonsoles", "López-Pernas", email = "sonsoles.lopez@uef.fi",
           role = c("aut", "cph")),
    person("Kamila", "Misiejuk", role = c("aut", "cph")))
Description: Builds co-occurrence networks from delimited fields, long/bipartite
    tables, binary matrices, wide sequences, or plain lists. Returns tidy
    edge data frames with eight similarity measures (Jaccard, cosine,
    association strength, etc.) and optional scaling. Converts results to
    'igraph', 'cograph', 'Nestimate', or 'tidygraph' objects. Network
    construction and analysis methods follow Saqr, Lopez-Pernas, Conde,
    and Hernandez-Garcia (2024, <doi:10.1007/978-3-031-54464-4_15>).
